_json.gridTitle: Georgia Beekeepers Association - I saw this fascinating post about using micro-fiber cloths to trap small hive beetles.  The theory is the bees chew the tips of the cloth, fraying it up slightly, and the beetles get tangled up in it and can't escape.  I thought too good to be true, but one of the commenters on the  thread posted the following pic.  I think I'm going to try it out! | Facebook
